lead_paragraph: The deeply divided town of Burns, Oregon, braced Monday for possible tension between demonstrators on both sides of an armed occupation of a federal wildlife refuge, days after one of the occupiers was shot dead by state police.

headline.main: Oregon Town Tense Amid Dueling Protests Over Armed Takeover of Wildlife Refuge
headline.print_headline: Oregon Town Tense Amid Dueling Protests Over Armed Takeover of Wildlife Refuge
